race.comment: ARIZONA LUCK (12) is a talented filly who was beaten 3L last time out in the tougher Thousand Guineas Prelude won by Ferivia over 1400m. There was a stack of merit in the effort, and this is a much more suitable assignment. Maps well and has plenty of scope for improvement. DANCING DOLLY (11) was much too good for a Maiden field over this trip at Kilmore, scoring by 3 lengths. Was heavily bet and will be fitter again. She should be right in it. GEE TEE (13) jumped awkwardly then wound up strongly to score by a long neck over 1400m here, breaking her Maiden. In a sharp local stable and is sure to keep improving. Will spot a start but wind up late and is among the chances again. TOUCHDOWN (1) next best. Won his maiden nicely first up at Sale.
